{"id": "ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE", "rating": 4.2, "userRatingCount": 64, "displayName": {"text": "Itani Sushi - Berkeley", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21acmFIbEJSbGRvUjFoWmVYQndUMFYwZEdWSFoxRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "The fish was the freshest I’ve had in a while, and the portions were worth the price for sure. They upgraded my tuna to toro for free on my 8 piece sashimi set, and it was so good! The toro was marbled so nicely that it looked like wagyu on the plate. I thought the nigiri and maki set was well selected. I will definitely be coming back! The owner/workers were super friendly and very knowledgeable.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "The fish was the freshest I’ve had in a while, and the portions were worth the price for sure. They upgraded my tuna to toro for free on my 8 piece sashimi set, and it was so good! The toro was marbled so nicely that it looked like wagyu on the plate. I thought the nigiri and maki set was well selected. I will definitely be coming back! The owner/workers were super friendly and very knowledgeable.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Yufei Huang", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106741854202280396774/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjHlSS9atq5mJ2ehC6rcma40mBV4TsYQbXFNnHvsplvqrG3hLrjw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-26T03:57:25.404674667Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21acmFIbEJSbGRvUjFoWmVYQndUMFYwZEdWSFoxRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21acmFIbEJSbGRvUjFoWmVYQndUMFYwZEdWSFoxRRAB!2m1!1s0x80857f6f57452b75:0x31ca5b68f4853644"}, {"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUVNVcFJWbDlQTWt0RlRVcHNTRkZvWDFsWWVXYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "I ordered takeout through DoorDash and was really impressed! I got 4 pieces of nigiri, Hosomaki, and Inari Combo. It came with 2 pieces of Sake nigiri, 2 pieces of Albacore Nigiri, 8 pieces of sake hosomaki roll, and 1 piece of Spicy Tuna stuffed inari pouch! The fish was fresh, the portion was decent, and the flavors were spot on. The price was also reasonable. They are located in a food hall, the first spot on the right when you enter the building. Highly recommended!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I ordered takeout through DoorDash and was really impressed! I got 4 pieces of nigiri, Hosomaki, and Inari Combo. It came with 2 pieces of Sake nigiri, 2 pieces of Albacore Nigiri, 8 pieces of sake hosomaki roll, and 1 piece of Spicy Tuna stuffed inari pouch! The fish was fresh, the portion was decent, and the flavors were spot on. The price was also reasonable. They are located in a food hall, the first spot on the right when you enter the building. Highly recommended!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Alice Hou", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118209491174900771446/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDlKWFVtHXfi5RlpYkOa9AJ3kzi4zvRKi2-61rc7TPsbKteJB7RQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-07T17:16:56.499939515Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUVNVcFJWbDlQTWt0RlRVcHNTRkZvWDFsWWVXYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUVNVcFJWbDlQTWt0RlRVcHNTRkZvWDFsWWVXYxAB!2m1!1s0x80857f6f57452b75:0x31ca5b68f4853644"}, {"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGelRHOXRlazB0UXpFMVN5MHhTWGx6VFVwWldsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "The 10 piece nigiri set is an amazing deal. I added an uni nigiri and was happy I did. Itani was recommended to me by a friend and I had it bookmarked - so glad I did! I was in the area and this was the perfect quick and delicious meal I needed. If I lived closer, I’d be here all the time. I highly recommend giving it a try!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "The 10 piece nigiri set is an amazing deal. I added an uni nigiri and was happy I did. Itani was recommended to me by a friend and I had it bookmarked - so glad I did! I was in the area and this was the perfect quick and delicious meal I needed. If I lived closer, I’d be here all the time. I highly recommend giving it a try!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Simone Park", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114780614357492288358/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0wnY9-V-bOGpizVOERGRzPvdDCIC2irKioEo8nNYAsTi2I_4OTQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-16T18:24:00.347440159Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGelRHOXRlazB0UXpFMVN5MHhTWGx6VFVwWldsRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGelRHOXRlazB0UXpFMVN5MHhTWGx6VFVwWldsRRAB!2m1!1s0x80857f6f57452b75:0x31ca5b68f4853644"}, {"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xOWmRqVXdTRkpIWlUxWWJIWnVSemRrVURCa1VYYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I’ve been a huge fan of Hopscotch, Itani Ramen, and Yonsei Handrolls for years, and I was beyond excited to see that the same group was opening a sushi spot in the Gourmet Ghetto! Of course I had to try it with a friend 😅\n\nWe each ordered a three-course sushi set and decided on the ITSU set and the baller set. We also added some miso soups and eventually more nigiri, including their delicious Hokkaido scallops and fantastic Hokkaido uni, both of which were about half the price I usually see when eating sushi in the Bay Area, Seattle, Hawaii, and New York. The arctic char was also phenomenal 🤤 (I should probably mention that I didn’t confirm that the scallops and uni were from Hokkaido, but the uni had that sweet butter consistency that I’ve only seen with Hokkaido uni.)\n\nFor drinks we both had still water, and my friend tried the iced tea. I went with the yuzu lemonade, which was delicious and perfect for the warm day but threatened to overwhelm my pallette at times. Service was prompt, generally lovely, and better than most of the service I’ve experienced across multiple states in the last few weeks (including other Bay Area restaurants). They also have different soy sauces available, and both of the ones we tried (I think it was the Yonsei house soy sauce and a garlic soy sauce?) were delicious!\n\nItani Sushi also had a bunch of freshly made to go options that looked like a perfect option for those in a bit of a hurry or wanting to enjoy the sunshine and some fresh air in their gorgeous, shared back patio (accessible if you walk past the bathrooms and towards the back of the building). I will 100% be back and look forward to my next visit!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I’ve been a huge fan of Hopscotch, Itani Ramen, and Yonsei Handrolls for years, and I was beyond excited to see that the same group was opening a sushi spot in the Gourmet Ghetto! Of course I had to try it with a friend 😅\n\nWe each ordered a three-course sushi set and decided on the ITSU set and the baller set. We also added some miso soups and eventually more nigiri, including their delicious Hokkaido scallops and fantastic Hokkaido uni, both of which were about half the price I usually see when eating sushi in the Bay Area, Seattle, Hawaii, and New York. The arctic char was also phenomenal 🤤 (I should probably mention that I didn’t confirm that the scallops and uni were from Hokkaido, but the uni had that sweet butter consistency that I’ve only seen with Hokkaido uni.)\n\nFor drinks we both had still water, and my friend tried the iced tea. I went with the yuzu lemonade, which was delicious and perfect for the warm day but threatened to overwhelm my pallette at times. Service was prompt, generally lovely, and better than most of the service I’ve experienced across multiple states in the last few weeks (including other Bay Area restaurants). They also have different soy sauces available, and both of the ones we tried (I think it was the Yonsei house soy sauce and a garlic soy sauce?) were delicious!\n\nItani Sushi also had a bunch of freshly made to go options that looked like a perfect option for those in a bit of a hurry or wanting to enjoy the sunshine and some fresh air in their gorgeous, shared back patio (accessible if you walk past the bathrooms and towards the back of the building). I will 100% be back and look forward to my next visit!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Helen Yamamoto", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110803582026408084386/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsNcuk-chlI6Gy6ZPqf8YlHqR5Ww3FGsC3jRq-X4PjgcBk6Fre=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2025-07-11T20:16:24.425791589Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xOWmRqVXdTRkpIWlUxWWJIWnVSemRrVURCa1VYYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xOWmRqVXdTRkpIWlUxWWJIWnVSemRrVURCa1VYYxAB!2m1!1s0x80857f6f57452b75:0x31ca5b68f4853644"}, {"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGR1VHWnNiRlpSWTB0SE1uSnRPV0pVUWpBM05GRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I wish I had a picture but the chirashi was fantastic. The fish was high quality and very fresh, the rice tasted amazing and the garnish included some very tasty Japanese basil. Overall well worth visiting.\n\nThe place is small with 12 bar style seating, so it’s really order, eat and go. Food was delivered promptly and served was knowledgeable and courteous. We ended up ordering a bucket of chicken from the sister restaurant across the way and the added it to the bill and even packed up what we could not finish.\n\nWonderful place and we will return.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I wish I had a picture but the chirashi was fantastic. The fish was high quality and very fresh, the rice tasted amazing and the garnish included some very tasty Japanese basil. Overall well worth visiting.\n\nThe place is small with 12 bar style seating, so it’s really order, eat and go. Food was delivered promptly and served was knowledgeable and courteous. We ended up ordering a bucket of chicken from the sister restaurant across the way and the added it to the bill and even packed up what we could not finish.\n\nWonderful place and we will return.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jeff Chalmers", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113607280873103388125/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpqK45rVT9fJMj7PQNS8RCdPGdpBZoRcI1_zctviQK_7_tFgWk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-17T14:57:36.648434772Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGR1VHWnNiRlpSWTB0SE1uSnRPV0pVUWpBM05GRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGR1VHWnNiRlpSWTB0SE1uSnRPV0pVUWpBM05GRRAB!2m1!1s0x80857f6f57452b75:0x31ca5b68f4853644"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJdStFV29_hYARRDaF9GhbyjE/photos/AWCwydjQAg6UPHMbYKmK-z-G28EZ0CD6zTTSMPPjZnQPr_gmmN5l2I2RPJ8s_-qiPNM3CnwKfkwAODhlM8uW7J5CFDA70y94a9HFsgPQBtMZY-fE9J-Lg5-ccGwNr0JJ-f-1g